         <abstract>
            <p>A class of k-block implicit hybrid methods for solving the initial value problem for ordinary differential equations are studied, which take a block of k new values at each step. These methods are examined for the property of A-stability. It is shown that the method of order 2k + 2 exists uniquely, and these methods are A-stable for block sizes k=1, 2,..., 5.</p>
         </abstract>
